name: Geology Club - General Interest Meeting Fall 2023
description:
Welcome to the Geology Club! We are holding a General Interest Meeting in Room 231 of Wright Rieman Laboratories on Busch campus on Tuesday, September 12th at 7:00pm.

Learn about all of the fun trips and cool events our club holds throughout the year, such as Grad Night, Career Night, trips to the Sterling Hill Mine Museum and other local geological spots. We also get involved in events with the Department of Earth and Planetary Sciences like the Oktoberfest, Holiday Party and more! 

We'll go on hiking trips, hold educational lectures, and bring students to the sectional and national GSA meetings to be exposed to the earth sciences!

name: Intro to AMSA
description:
Join us on September 12th for our first general member meeting of the 2023-24 year! At this meeting, we will introduce our executive board, explain some of our plans for the semester as well as gain insight into some of the expectations you have for us. Our e-board has been working hard over the summer to make AMSA a place for pre-health students to come and learn more about what their future entails and receive guidance from upperclassmen and hope you can make it.

We are looking forward to meeting everyone!

If you haven't already join our mailing list!
